<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">
[TL: Kushdjula, Taurus Mountains; Das Dagh, Amanus Mountains, 
<collectingCountry box="[1364,1432,151,177]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Hatay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,237,186,213]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Turkey</collectingCountry>
]; syntypic material consists of a single male and 
<specimenCount box="[793,930,187,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
in the Naturhistorisches Museum in Vienna, each having a red ‘type’ label. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesselbarth, G. &amp; van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S." box="[483,773,222,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 847" refId="ref9287" refString="Hesselbarth, G., van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S. (1995) Die Tagfalter der Turkei unter Berucksichtigung der angrenzenden Lander, Sigbert Wagener, Bocholt, Germany, 1, 1 - 757, 2, 758 - 1354, 3, 1 - 847." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hesselbarth 
<emphasis box="[620,675,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
(1995: 2
</bibRefCitation>
, 1031) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[899,1283,223,250]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 63)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised this subspecies with 
<emphasis box="[379,654,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1876" box="[379,578,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="punica">M. phoebe punica</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[584,654,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">telona</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[706,813,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis box="[706,813,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively; the present authors certainly consider that this subspecies belongs to either 
<taxonomicName box="[516,628,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis box="[516,628,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[664,771,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis box="[664,771,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1022,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[904,1022,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Bereczki, J. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Rota, J. &amp; Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[1034,1231,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" pagination="749 - 757" refId="ref11329" refString="Toth, J. P., Bereczki, J., Varga, Z., Rota, J., Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2014) Relationships within the Melitaea phoebe species group (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae): new insights from molecular and morphometric information. Systematic Entomology, 39, 749 - 757. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12083" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tóth 
<emphasis box="[1094,1150,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
demonstrated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[151,260,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis box="[151,260,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was present in 
<collectingCountry box="[439,540,331,357]" name="Lebanon" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
, to the South of the Nur mountain range and 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, P. J. C. &amp; Pateman, J. E." box="[1058,1358,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" pagination="85 - 94" refId="ref10812" refString="Russell, P. J. C. &amp; Pateman, J. E. (2012) Some observations on populations of Melitaea telona Fruhstorfer, 1908 (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae) in Turkey. Entomologist's Gazette, 63, 85 - 94." type="journal article" year="2012">Russell &amp; Pateman (2012)</bibRefCitation>
reared an egg batch from a female captured at Tuzlabeli geçidi, Muðla, western 
<collectingCountry box="[987,1067,367,393]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and demonstrated from the L4+ larval head colour that the population there was not 
<taxonomicName box="[749,869,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[749,869,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<taxonomicName box="[922,1036,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis box="[922,1036,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The first author considers that the specimens should probably be associated with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[679,787,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis box="[679,787,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but further DNA analysis is required to confirm to which species they belong. In order that this subspecific name can be in future firmly associated with a species we hereby formally designate the male specimen as 
<typeStatus box="[611,714,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Rebel, 1917" authorityName=", Rebel" authorityYear="1917" box="[760,1125,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="amanica">
<emphasis box="[760,980,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. phoebe amanica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rebel, H." box="[987,1125,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" pagination="243 - 282" refId="ref10458" refString="Rebel, H. (1917) Eine Lepidopterenausbeute aus dem Amanusgebirge (Alman Dagh). Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Wien, 126, 243 - 282." type="journal article" year="1917">Rebel, 1917</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. From figures 13A, B it can be seen that this specimen has the wing morphological characters typical of both 
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1196,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis box="[1082,1196,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1253,1362,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis box="[1253,1362,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[304,422,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[304,422,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The labels on the specimen pin (
<figureCitation box="[801,901,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,623,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-232@6.[151,1436,597,1888]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. 13, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe amanica, Rebel, 1917. 14, Lectotype male of Melitaea phoebe dorae Graves, 1925. 15, Paralectotype male of Melitaea phoebe dorae Graves, 1925. 16, Holotype of Melitaea phoebe enoch Higgins, 1941. Fig. 13 © H. Bruckner. Figs 14–16 © J. Tennent.A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577644/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
) are as follows: (1) on white paper handwritten in black “Taurus/ Kushdjula/ 22.V.14”; (2) on white paper handwritten in black “ 
<emphasis box="[1077,1271,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName box="[1077,1153,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">phoebe</taxonomicName>
/ amanica
</emphasis>
/ Type [in red] Rbl”; (3) on white card typed in black “Misident:/ 
<taxonomicName authority=", Russell 2021" authorityName=", Russell" authorityYear="2021" box="[723,1065,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis box="[723,900,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Melitaea telona</emphasis>
, Russell 2021
</taxonomicName>
”; (4) on red paper typed in black “ 
<typeStatus box="[160,322,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Rebel" authorityYear="1917" box="[338,628,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="amanica">
<emphasis box="[338,628,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Melitaea phoebe amanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<bibRefCitation author="Rebel, H." box="[644,801,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" pagination="243 - 282" refId="ref10458" refString="Rebel, H. (1917) Eine Lepidopterenausbeute aus dem Amanusgebirge (Alman Dagh). Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Wien, 126, 243 - 282." type="journal article" year="1917">REBEL, 1917</bibRefCitation>
/ designated Russell &amp;/ Gaal-Haszler 2021”.
</paragraph>
